---
import Base from '~/layouts/Base.astro';
import { SITE, STATS } from '~/data/site';
---
<Base title="About" description="Way4Tech is an Odoo customization and implementation specialist serving clients in Pakistan and the GCC. Founded by Waqas Riasat.">
  <section class="bg-gradient-to-br from-brand-950 to-brand-800 text-white">
    <div class="container-site py-16 sm:py-24">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <div class="eyebrow text-brand-200">About {SITE.name}</div>
        <h1 class="h1 mt-4">Engineers who ship. Support that stays.</h1>
        <p class="lede mt-6 text-ink-100">{SITE.name} is a specialist Odoo firm. We don't do WordPress, we don't do Shopify. We do Odoo — and we do it deeply.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container-site">
      <div class="grid gap-14 lg:grid-cols-3">
        <div class="lg:col-span-2 prose prose-ink max-w-none">
          <h2 class="h3">Our story</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-ink-700">
            Way4Tech started with a simple observation: most Odoo partners treat ERP like a one-time project. You sign a contract, they configure some modules, they disappear. Six months later you're paying someone else to fix it.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-4 text-ink-700">
            We do it differently. We write clean code that your next developer can read. We support production the same way we built it — with senior engineers, not ticket queues. We stay in touch with our clients for years, not months.
          </p>

          <h2 class="h3 mt-12">What we believe</h2>
          <ul class="mt-6 space-y-4">
            <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-brand-600 font-bold mt-1">→</span><div><strong class="text-ink-900">Extend Odoo — don't fight it.</strong><p class="text-ink-600 mt-1">We inherit from Odoo's base models. We don't create parallel universes that break on every upgrade.</p></div></li>
            <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-brand-600 font-bold mt-1">→</span><div><strong class="text-ink-900">Community-first.</strong><p class="text-ink-600 mt-1">Most of what you need can be built on Odoo Community. We recommend Enterprise only when it genuinely pays off.</p></div></li>
            <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-brand-600 font-bold mt-1">→</span><div><strong class="text-ink-900">Own the outcome.</strong><p class="text-ink-600 mt-1">If something breaks in production at 2am, that's on us. No finger-pointing at the hosting provider or the theme.</p></div></li>
            <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-brand-600 font-bold mt-1">→</span><div><strong class="text-ink-900">No feature we haven't used.</strong><p class="text-ink-600 mt-1">Before we ship a module to a client, it's been running in our own operations for weeks.</p></div></li>
          </ul>

          <h2 class="h3 mt-12">Where we work</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-ink-700">
            Our team is based in Pakistan. We serve clients across Pakistan, the UAE, and Saudi Arabia — with deployments in healthcare, retail, POS, logistics, manufacturing, and services. Remote-first with occasional on-site visits for major rollouts.
          </p>
        </div>

        <aside class="lg:col-span-1">
          <div class="rounded-2xl bg-ink-50 p-6">
            <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold">By the numbers</h3>
            <div class="mt-4 grid grid-cols-2 gap-4">
              {STATS.map((s) => (
                <div>
                  <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-700">{s.value}</div>
                  <div class="text-xs text-ink-600 mt-1">{s.label}</div>
                </div>
              ))}
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="rounded-2xl border border-ink-200 bg-white p-6 mt-6">
            <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold">Get in touch</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-ink-600">Have a question or want to work together?</p>
            <a href="/contact/" class="btn-primary w-full mt-5">Contact us</a>
          </div>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
